data.text:
Exams accepted at Regent's University London for the academic year 2023-2024.

Regent's University London is a prestigious institution that offers undergraduate (UG), postgraduate (PG), and Ph.D. programs across various disciplines. The university accepts different exams for admission, depending on the level of study. Here is a tabular format presenting the exams accepted for each category:

Level of Study Accepted Exams Undergraduate - SAT (Scholastic Assessment Test) - ACT (American College Test) - A-levels or AS-levels (General Certificate of Education) - International Baccalaureate (IB) Diploma - High School Diploma (for North American applicants) Postgraduate - GMAT (Graduate Management Admission Test) - GRE (Graduate Record Examination) - English Language Proficiency Test (e.g., IELTS, TOEFL) Ph.D. - Relevant Master's degree - Research proposal and interview

Please note that the above list is not exhaustive and the university may have specific requirements for different programs. It is always recommended to visit the official website of Regent's University London or contact the admissions office for the most accurate and up-to-date information.

Regent's University London is a prestigious institution known for producing highly accomplished graduates who have made significant contributions in various fields. Here are some notable alumni who have studied at Regent's University London:

Jonathan Powell - Jonathan Powell is a British diplomat and politician who served as the Chief of Staff to former Prime Minister Tony Blair. He played a crucial role in the Northern Ireland peace process and has been involved in numerous international negotiations.

Sahar Hashemi - Sahar Hashemi is an entrepreneur and bestselling author. She co-founded the coffee chain Coffee Republic, which revolutionized the coffee industry in the UK. She is also known for her advocacy of entrepreneurship and innovation.

Hamdi Ulukaya - Hamdi Ulukaya is a Turkish-American businessman and the founder of Chobani, one of the leading Greek yogurt brands in the United States. He has been recognized for his commitment to social entrepreneurship and philanthropy.

Karin Wanngård - Karin Wanngård is a Swedish politician who served as the Mayor of Stockholm from 2014 to 2018. She has been actively involved in urban development and sustainability initiatives, focusing on creating a greener and more inclusive city.

Nalini Sivathasan - Nalini Sivathasan is a renowned journalist and news anchor, known for her work with BBC News. She has reported on major global events and has conducted interviews with influential figures across various industries.
